quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Conditional Statements[/h1]

[b]Conditional statements[/b] perform different actions for different decisions.
The [b]if else[/b] statement is used to execute a certain code if a condition is [b]true[/b], and another code if the condition is [b]false[/b].
[b]Syntax:[/b][code format="php" ][b]if[/b] (condition) {
   code to be executed if condition is [b]true[/b];
} [b]else [/b]{
   code to be executed if condition is [b]false[/b];
}[/code]
[note]You can also use the[b] if[/b] statement without the [b]else [/b]statement, if you do not need to do anything, in case the condition is [b]false[/b].[/note]

quizzes.question:
